NAME: ST Francis Community Laboratory
F9_03_PROG_DESC: St. Francis Community Laboratory ("St. Francis") is a pathology laboratory located in Leon, Nicaragua. St. Francis provides diagnostic testing, screenings and biopsies to hospitals, physicians and community clinics in the Leon, Nicaragua area.Due to the current political regime in Nicaragua, laboratories performing such services are only allowed to be paid at the contractual rate established by the goverment. The goverment-mandated payment rates for pathology services are far below the actual cost of providing such services. Due to this discrepency, pathology laboratories are unable to provide much-needed medical tests to the people of Nicaragua without additional funding. In addition, the current turnaround times for some diagnostic tests are extremely long. St. Francis provides the people of Nicaragua with the necessary tests on an expediated basis.In addition, St. Francis provides funds pathology services to other non-profit organizations (such as Doctors Without Borders) that provide free or low cost health and medical services in and around Leon, Nicaragua.

NAME: UNITED WAY OF ESSEX AND WEST HUDSON
F9_03_PROG_DESC: RESOURCE INVESTMENT:THIS PROGRAM IS RESPONSIBLE FOR DISTRIBUTING THE FINANCIAL RESOURCES LEVERAGED FROM CORPORATE AND PRIVATE DONATIONS. IT IS ADMINISTERED BY THE COMMUNITY IMPACT STAFF AND SEEKS TO CARRY OUT THE CONTRIBUTORS' INTENT BASED ON ADEQUATE KNOWLEDGE OF OUR SERVICE AREA'S PRIORITY NEEDS IN EDUCATION, HEALTH AND INCOME. THIS ALSO INCLUDES WORKING WITH AGENCIES TO HELP BUILD THEIR CAPACITY TO DELIVER EFFECTIVE SERVICES THROUGH OUR CENTER FOR EXCELLENCE TRAINING PROGRAM AS WELL AS ASSISTING SERVICE PROVIDERS IN RESPONDING TO COMMUNITY PROBLEMS.
F9_03_PROG_DESC.1: INFORMATION & REFERRAL AND CRISIS RESPONSE & 2-1-1:THIS PROGRAM IS CHARGED WITH SERVING AS A CENTRAL SOURCE OF INFORMATION ABOUT HEALTH, WELFARE, BASIC NEEDS AND VOLUNTEER OPPORTUNITIES IN THE COMMUNITY. THROUGH INFORMATION AND REFERRAL, UNITED WAY PROVIDES A SITE WHERE INTERESTED, TRAINED INDIVIDUALS CAN CONNECT INDIVIDUALS TO A SERVICE OR OPPORTUNITY. THROUGH THE CRISIS RESPONSE UNIT, UNITED WAY CONTINUES TO WORK NOT ONLY WITH INDIVIDUALS WHO WERE AFFECTED BY 9/11, BUT ALSO WORKS WITH THE NON-PROFIT COMMUNITY AND GOVERNMENT AGENCIES TO ENSURE PREPAREDNESS TO RESPOND IN THE EVENT OF A FUTURE CRISIS.
